    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix M2SetupFailure message encoding in MCE_send_M2_SETUP_FAILURE\n\n### Summary\nThe `MCE_send_M2_SETUP_FAILURE` function was not properly using the `m2ap_setup_failure` parameter to set the appropriate values in the outgoing M2SetupFailure message. Instead, it was hardcoding the cause and ignoring the optional TimeToWait and CriticalityDiagnostics IEs even when they should have been included based on the parameter values.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE_interface_management.c`: Modified `MCE_send_M2_SETUP_FAILURE` to properly use the `m2ap_setup_failure` parameter for setting the cause, TimeToWait, and CriticalityDiagnostics IEs.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen the MCE receives an M2SetupRequest that cannot be processed successfully, it should send an M2SetupFailure message with appropriate cause and optional IEs based on the failure context. However, due to the hardcoded implementation, the outgoing message always contained the same cause regardless of the actual failure reason, and optional IEs were never included even when the calling code provided values for them.\n\nThis could lead to interoperability issues with eNBs that expect specific cause values or optional IEs in M2SetupFailure messages, potentially causing the eNB to retry M2 setup indefinitely or fail to establish the M2 interface properly.\n"
}